#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:1
msgid "Building using emscripten for WebAssembly"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:3
msgid "Introduction"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:5
msgid ""
"This page describes how to build and install VTK using [emscripten](https://"
"emscripten.org) on any platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:9
msgid "Guide created using"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:11
msgid "CMake 3.31.3"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:12
msgid "Ninja 1.12.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:13
msgid "Emscripten 4.0.20"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:14
msgid "NodeJS 24.0.1"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:15
msgid "Chrome For Testing 133.0.6943.98"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:18
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:20
msgid "For this guide, you will need the following:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:22
msgid ""
"**CMake**: [CMake](http://www.cmake.org/) version 3.29 or higher and Ninja. "
"CMake is a tool that makes cross-platform building simple. On several "
"systems it will probably be already installed. If it is not, please use the "
"following instructions to install it.  There are several precompiled "
"binaries available at the [CMake download page](https://cmake.org/"
"download/). Add CMake to your PATH environment variable if you downloaded an "
"archive and not an installer."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:29
msgid ""
"**Emscripten SDK**: [emsdk](https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk) and "
"any dependencies needed by emsdk.  Emscripten is a complete compiler "
"toolchain to WebAssembly, using LLVM, with a special focus on speed, size, "
"and the Web platform."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:34
msgid ""
"**Node.js**: NodeJS will be used as a cross compiling emulator by CMake to "
"run the generated JavaScript files"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:37
msgid ""
"**VTK source-code**: You can either click the download button to get an "
"archive containing the latest version of VTK-git or clone the repository "
"(only recommended if you wish to contribute to VTK). In the last case, see "
"[git/develop.md](../developers_guide/git/develop.md)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:41
msgid ""
"**Chrome For Testing**: This is optional. It is useful if you intend to run "
"the test suite with `ctest`. This is a Chrome flavor that specifically "
"targets web app testing and automation use cases. Please download the "
"133.0.6943.98 version from [vtk.org/files/support](https://vtk.org/files/"
"support)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:45
msgid "Install prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:0
msgid "macOS/Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:51
msgid ""
"# Download and install fnm:\n"
"curl -o- https://fnm.vercel.app/install | bash\n"
"# Download and install Node.js\n"
"fnm install 24.0.1\n"
"fnm use 24.0.1\n"
"\n"
"# Download and install EMSDK\n"
"git clone https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk.git\n"
"./emsdk/emsdk install 4.0.20\n"
"export PATH=$PWD/emsdk/upstream/bin:$PWD/emsdk/upstream/emscripten:$PATH\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:0
msgid "Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:66
msgid ""
"# In Powershell\n"
"# Download and install fnm:\n"
"winget install Schniz.fnm\n"
"# Download and install Node.js\n"
"fnm install 24.0.1\n"
"fnm env --use-on-cd --shell power-shell | Out-String | Invoke-Expression\n"
"fnm use 24.0.1\n"
"\n"
"git clone https://github.com/emscripten-core/emsdk.git\n"
".\\emsdk\\emsdk install 4.0.20\n"
"$env:PATH=\"$PWD\\emsdk\\upstream\\bin;$PWD\\emsdk\\upstream\\emscripten;"
"$env:PATH\"\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:82
msgid "Build project"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:84
msgid "The following environment variables are assumed:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:86
msgid ""
"`VTK_SOURCE_DIR`: Specifies the path to the root directory of the VTK source "
"code. This variable should point to the location where the VTK source files "
"are located and is used as the input for the build process."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:87
msgid ""
"`VTK_BUILD_DIR`: Defines the directory where the VTK build artifacts will be "
"generated. This is typically a separate directory from the source to allow "
"for out-of-source builds and to keep build files organized."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:88
msgid ""
"`VTK_INSTALL_DIR`: Indicates the target directory where the built VTK "
"libraries and headers will be installed after the build process completes. "
"This allows for easy access and reuse of the compiled VTK components."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:90
msgid "Configure and build"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:0
msgid "wasm32:macOS/Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:96
msgid ""
"emcmake cmake \\\n"
"  -S ${VTK_SOURCE_DIR} \\\n"
"  -B ${VTK_BUILD_DIR} \\\n"
"  -G \"Ninja\" \\\n"
"  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \\\n"
"  \"-DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=OFF\" \\\n"
"  \"-DVTK_ENABLE_WEBGPU:BOOL=ON\"\n"
"cmake --build ${VTK_BUILD_DIR}\n"
"cmake --install ${VTK_BUILD_DIR} --prefix ${VTK_INSTALL_DIR}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:0
msgid "wasm64:macOS/Linux"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:110
msgid ""
"emcmake cmake \\\n"
"  -S ${VTK_SOURCE_DIR} \\\n"
"  -B ${VTK_BUILD_DIR} \\\n"
"  -G \"Ninja\" \\\n"
"  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release \\\n"
"  \"-DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=OFF\" \\\n"
"  \"-DVTK_ENABLE_WEBGPU:BOOL=ON\" \\\n"
"  \"-DVTK_WEBASSEMBLY_64_BIT:BOOL=ON\"\n"
"cmake --build ${VTK_BUILD_DIR}\n"
"cmake --install ${VTK_BUILD_DIR} --prefix ${VTK_INSTALL_DIR}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:0
msgid "wasm32:Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:125
msgid ""
"# In Powershell\n"
"emcmake cmake `\n"
"  -S $env:VTK_SOURCE_DIR `\n"
"  -B $env:VTK_BUILD_DIR `\n"
"  -G \"Ninja\" `\n"
"  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release `\n"
"  \"-DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=OFF\" `\n"
"  \"-DVTK_ENABLE_WEBGPU:BOOL=ON\"\n"
"cmake --build $env:VTK_BUILD_DIR\n"
"cmake --install $env:VTK_BUILD_DIR --prefix $env:VTK_INSTALL_DIR\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:0
msgid "wasm64:Windows"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:140
msgid ""
"# In Powershell\n"
"emcmake cmake `\n"
"  -S $env:VTK_SOURCE_DIR `\n"
"  -B $env:VTK_BUILD_DIR `\n"
"  -G \"Ninja\" `\n"
"  -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release `\n"
"  \"-DBUILD_SHARED_LIBS:BOOL=OFF\" `\n"
"  \"-DVTK_ENABLE_WEBGPU:BOOL=ON\" `\n"
"  \"-DVTK_WEBASSEMBLY_64_BIT:BOOL=ON\"\n"
"cmake --build $env:VTK_BUILD_DIR\n"
"cmake --install $env:VTK_BUILD_DIR --prefix $env:VTK_INSTALL_DIR\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:157
msgid ""
"When copy pasting the commands on windows, please paste them into a "
"Powershell window and not a Command prompt!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../advanced/build_wasm_emscripten.md:160
msgid ""
"In order to run the unit tests, please enable testing with `-"
"DVTK_BUILD_TESTING=WANT`. Additionally, specify the browser that shall be "
"used to run the wasm unit test with `-DVTK_TESTING_WASM_ENGINE:FILEPATH=/"
